      • addUniqueLabel

        public java.lang.String addUniqueLabel(java.lang.String prefix,
                                       java.util.BitSet labelStates,
                                       java.util.Set<java.lang.String> definedLabelNames)
        Add a label with corresponding state set, ensuring a unique, non-existing label. The label will be either "X" or "X_i" where X is the content of the prefix argument and i is a non-negative integer.
        Optionally, a set of defined label names can be passed so that those labels can be avoided. This can be obtained from the model checker via getDefinedLabelNames().
        Note that a stored label takes precedence over the on-the-fly calculation of an ExpressionLabel, cf. StateModelChecker.checkExpressionLabel(explicit.Model, parser.ast.ExpressionLabel, java.util.BitSet)
        Parameters:
        prefix - the prefix for the unique label
        labelStates - the BitSet with the state set for the label
        definedLabelNames - set of names (optional, may be null) to check for existing labels
        Returns:
        the generated unique label
